newsitem.title: THAILAND: Thai interbank rate, baht ease in late trade.
newsitem.headline: Thai interbank rate, baht ease in late trade.

text.p: The Thai overnight interbank rate eased to 6.00-7.00 percent in late trade on Wednesday from 9.00 percent earlier and 9.50 percent late on Tuesday on a high money supply, dealers said.
"The market was very quiet in the afternoon as most banks already have funds for reserve requirements tomorrow," said a dealer at a local bank. "The rate should fall further tomorrow."
Dealers said low swap interest rates also prompted some banks to bring in cheap offshore funds.
